  "prompt": "What do Pakistani citizens think about Uri Attack?",
  "response": "The Uri Attack of September 18, 2016, was a terrorist attack on an Indian Army base in Uri, Jammu and Kashmir, where 19 Indian soldiers were killed. Pakistani citizens had mixed reactions to this incident:\n\n1. Official Pakistani stance:\n- Condemned the attack\n- Denied involvement\n- Rejected India's accusations of Pakistan's role\n\n2. Public reactions varied:\n- Some sympathized with the soldiers\n- Some supported militant groups\n- Many feared potential escalation of tensions\n- Some saw it as part of the ongoing Kashmir conflict\n\n3. Perspectives differed based on:\n- Political affiliation\n- Personal views on India-Pakistan relations\n- Understanding of the Kashmir issue\n\n4. Mainstream response:\n- Majority wanted peaceful resolution\n- Concerned about potential military confrontation\n- Hoped diplomatic channels would be used\n\n5. Political responses:\n- Government denied sponsoring terrorism\n- Some political groups supported resistance movements\n- Opposition parties had different interpretations\n\nIt's important to note that public opinion is diverse and cannot be generalized. Individual perspectives varied significantly across different segments of Pakistani society.",
